    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "text": "135",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "At that time the Air Force termed the Heflin pict-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "e a hoax.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "The \"Bluebook\" report said Heflin's photo did not",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "orrespond to his description of the round, saucer-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "e object.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "But since then the Air Force has commissioned",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "e independent study by the University of Colorado",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "Literature",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "»Piece for a jig-saw«",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "By LEONARD G. CARMP., M.S.I.A. A.R.Ae.S.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "author of \"Space, Gravity and the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "Flying Saucer.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "Two PCs spot a »saucer«",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "Two policemen saw an oval-shaped object flash",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "wrough the sky yesterday. The officers said the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "saucer-like object flew over Strood, Kent, at about",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "000 feet - and had a tail of blue and silvery stars.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Later there was a similar report from Sevenoaks,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "Kent.)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "Police at Rochester said: \"The authorities have",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "seen told.\"",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "From: \"Daily Sketch\", London, March 25th, 1967.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "Here is a book about \"flying saucers\" which can",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "be of immense interest to both the \"converted\" and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "those looking for more corroboration to back up his beliefs in the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "reality of visiting space-ships, and to the technically-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "minded man who may well be rather surprised at the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "wealth of detail of a highly technical nature included",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "in this work.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "Leonard Cramp, who for many many years has worked",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "in both aerodynamics and, more recently, with the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "new design principles of the Hovercraft, has succeeded in writing a bookunderstood, by any person",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "of normal intelligence who can read the English",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "language.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "\"Piece For A Jig-saw\" does, in truth, offer a piece",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "- a very large piece - of that enigmatic jig-saw",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "puzzle which has undulated and returned along 180",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "degrees through head-lines of the world's press for",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "the past 20 years. Cramp himself has worked on",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "material for this book for over half that time. It is",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "12 years since he submitted to the public \"Space,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "Gravity and the Flying Saucer\"; - this book is a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "natural and elevating follow-up.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "Written in a style which is as open and as lacking",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "in pomposity as the author himself, one finds a patt-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "text": "ern developing from each chapter to the next, as he",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "text": "takes us from his brief but concise \"background",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 55,
      "text": "material\" of orthodox aerodynamics, curves into a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 56,
      "text": "high trajectory through the experimental X-15 and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 57,
      "text": "the family of rockets, and into the deep blue. One",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 58,
      "text": "is almost shocked to find with what ease Cramp",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 59,
      "text": "brings us down - not in a capsule supported by",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 60,
      "text": "great billowing parachutes, but gently landing in a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 61,
      "text": "field, any field, ready for instant take-off to a far-off",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 62,
      "text": "hovering mother-ship.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 63,
      "text": "At least, the mother-ship is there by implication,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 64,
      "text": "because Mr. Cramp, as he says, having \"set myself",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 65,
      "text": "the task of discovering the truth as an engineer\",",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 66,
      "text": "arrives, after a volume full of investigation and ex-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 67,
      "text": "perimentation, at the last chapter which is entitled:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 68,
      "text": "\"Vindication Of A Scout Ship.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 69,
      "text": "The last paragraph of the second from last chapter",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 70,
      "text": "might well sum up a very large part of the UFO",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 71,
      "text": "story. It also sums up the author, a man who succ-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 72,
      "text": "eeded in forming a large group of UFO enthusiasts",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 73,
      "text": "from a very hard core of technology, men who knew",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 74,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 75,
      "text": "»The flying saucer that",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 76,
      "text": "Andrew saw in Stamford Sky«",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 77,
      "text": "Andrew, the eight-year-old son of Mr. and Mrs.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 78,
      "text": "T. H. Hyde, of 59 Scotgate, Stamford, claims to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 79,
      "text": "have seen a \"flying saucer\" over Stamford on Tues-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 80,
      "text": "day, Aug. 2. He was in his back garden at the time,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 81,
      "text": "and this is how he sketched and described what he",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 82,
      "text": "saw:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 83,
      "text": "\"I saw this object in the sky twice this morning",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 84,
      "text": "between about half-past ten and a quarter to eleven.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 85,
      "text": "It was going very quickly above the clouds. The",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 86,
      "text": "first time I saw it, it was travelling in a N. W.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 87,
      "text": "direction, and then about ten minutes later it came",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 88,
      "text": "back.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 89,
      "text": "\"It was then going in a S. E. direction, and it",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 90,
      "text": "made no sound. The shape was round, with black",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 91,
      "text": "circles looking like ship's port-holes round the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 92,
      "text": "middle. There were little things looking like landing",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 93,
      "text": "wheels on the bottom.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 94,
      "text": "\"There was a cloud of yellow stuff coming out",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 95,
      "text": "of the back and there was a ring round the middle",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 96,
      "text": "of the object.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 97,
      "text": "UNQUOTE.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 98,
      "text": "From: A Stamford paper, Lincs. England.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 99,
      "text": "August 1966.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 100,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 101,
      "text": "A friend is a person who knows all about",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 102,
      "text": "you - and still likes you. Elbert Hubbard.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    }
